verses.text: Doth not wisdom cry ? and understanding put forth her voice ?
She standeth in the top of high places , by the way in the places of the paths.
She crieth at the gates , at the entry of the city , at the coming in at the doors.
Unto you, O men , I call ; and my voice \add is\add* to the sons of man.
O ye simple , understand wisdom : and, ye fools , be ye of an understanding heart.
Hear ; for I will speak of excellent things ; and the opening of my lips \add shall be\add* right things.
For my mouth shall speak truth ; and wickedness \add is\add* an abomination to my lips.\f + \fr 8.7 \ft an…: Heb. the abomination of my lips\f*
All the words of my mouth \add are\add* in righteousness ; \add there is\add* nothing froward or perverse in them.\f + \fr 8.8 \ft froward: Heb. wreathed\f*
They \add are\add* all plain to him that understandeth , and right to them that find knowledge.
Receive my instruction , and not silver ; and knowledge rather than choice gold.
For wisdom \add is\add* better than rubies ; and all the things that may be desired are not to be compared to it. \p
I wisdom dwell with prudence , and find out knowledge of witty inventions.\f + \fr 8.12 \ft prudence: or, subtilty\f*
The fear of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* \add is\add* to hate evil : pride , and arrogancy , and the evil way , and the froward mouth , do I hate.
Counsel \add is\add* mine, and sound wisdom : I \add am\add* understanding ; I have strength.
By me kings reign , and princes decree justice.
By me princes rule , and nobles , \add even\add* all the judges of the earth.
I love them that love me; and those that seek me early shall find me.
Riches and honour \add are\add* with me; \add yea\add*, durable riches and righteousness.
My fruit \add is\add* better than gold , yea, than fine gold ; and my revenue than choice silver.
I lead in the way of righteousness , in the midst of the paths of judgment :\f + \fr 8.20 \ft lead: or, walk\f*
That I may cause those that love me to inherit substance ; and I will fill their treasures. \p
The \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* possessed me in the beginning of his way , before his works of old.
I was set up from everlasting , from the beginning , or ever the earth was.
When \add there were\add* no depths , I was brought forth ; when \add there were\add* no fountains abounding with water.
Before the mountains were settled , before the hills was I brought forth :

While as yet he had not made the earth , nor the fields , nor the highest part of the dust of the world.\f + \fr 8.26 \ft fields: or, open places\f*\f + \fr 8.26 \ft the highest…: or, the chief part\f*
When he prepared the heavens , I \add was\add* there: when he set a compass upon the face of the depth :\f + \fr 8.27 \ft a compass: or, a circle\f*
When he established the clouds above : when he strengthened the fountains of the deep :
When he gave to the sea his decree , that the waters should not pass his commandment : when he appointed the foundations of the earth :
Then I was by him , \add as\add* one brought up \add with him:\add* and I was daily \add his\add* delight , rejoicing always before him;
Rejoicing in the habitable part of his earth ; and my delights \add were\add* with the sons of men. \p
Now therefore hearken unto me, O ye children : for blessed \add are they that\add* keep my ways.
Hear instruction , and be wise , and refuse it not.
Blessed \add is\add* the man that heareth me, watching daily at my gates , waiting at the posts of my doors.
For whoso findeth me findeth life , and shall obtain favour of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*.\f + \fr 8.35 \ft obtain: Heb. bring forth\f*
But he that sinneth against me wrongeth his own soul : all they that hate me love death.
